---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Introduction - sls.tf">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="docs-header">
      <h1>Welcome to sls.tf</h1>
      <p class="docs-description">
        A comprehensive Terraform module for converting Serverless Framework applications to production-ready infrastructure
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="content">
      <section class="section">
        <h2>What is sls.tf?</h2>
        <p>
          sls.tf is a powerful Terraform module that transforms your Serverless Framework configurations
          into production-ready Terraform infrastructure. It provides a seamless bridge between the simplicity
          of Serverless Framework and the power and flexibility of Terraform.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <h2>Key Benefits</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Infrastructure as Code:</strong> Manage your serverless applications with Terraform best practices</li>
          <li><strong>Production Ready:</strong> Built-in security, monitoring, and disaster recovery capabilities</li>
          <li><strong>Comprehensive Support:</strong> Full support for Lambda functions, API Gateway, DynamoDB, and more</li>
          <li><strong>Advanced Features:</strong> Variable resolution, custom resources, and TypeScript configuration support</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <h2>How It Works</h2>
        <p>
          sls.tf reads your existing serverless.yml configuration and automatically generates the corresponding
          Terraform resources. This means you can continue using the familiar Serverless Framework syntax while
          leveraging Terraform's powerful infrastructure management capabilities.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <h2>What's Included</h2>
        <p>
          This comprehensive Terraform module includes:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Complete Lambda function support with all configurations</li>
          <li>API Gateway REST APIs with proper routing and security</li>
          <li>DynamoDB tables with automatic scaling and backup</li>
          <li>S3 buckets for static assets and file storage</li>
          <li>IAM roles and policies with principle of least privilege</li>
          <li>CloudWatch monitoring and logging</li>
          <li>VPC networking support for private resources</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <h2>Getting Started</h2>
        <p>
          Ready to convert your Serverless Framework application to Terraform? Check out our
          <a href="/docs/quick-start">Quick Start guide</a> to get up and running in minutes.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
  .container {
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 2rem;
  }

  .docs-header {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 4rem;
  }

  .docs-header h1 {
    font-size: 3rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #1a202c;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .docs-description {
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    color: #4a5568;
    max-width: 600px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .content {
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .section {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .section h2 {
    font-size: 1.8rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #1a202c;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    border-bottom: 2px solid #e2e8f0;
    padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .section p {
    color: #4a5568;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .section ul {
    margin: 1rem 0;
    padding-left: 2rem;
  }

  .section li {
    color: #4a5568;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .section a {
    color: #667eea;
    text-decoration: none;
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .section a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .container {
      padding: 1rem;
    }

    .docs-header h1 {
      font-size: 2rem;
    }

    .section h2 {
      font-size: 1.5rem;
    }
  }
</style>